File: The SACP in the North West says the case shouldn't be taken lightly. JOHANNESBURG - The South African Communist Party wants changes to tender procurement regulations. The party says it needs to be easier for normal citizens to apply and benefit from them. SACP: Govt needs to do more to fight corruption "We want to call on South Africans to embrace public property and public interest economy and to see what is done by our government as belonging to all of us. "We will continue to fight for this to ensure that the de-tenderisation of the state takes place," said SACP First Deputy Secretary, Solly Mapaila. The party says the changes will in turn grow the country's fragile economy.